Red Lentil Curry
http://www.kiddieliciouskitchen.com/easy-red-lentil-curry/
PREP TIME: 5 mins
COOK TIME: 30 mins
Serves: 4-6

*****   Cut this in half!!!   *****

1 cup red lentils
2 tbsp olive oil
1 onion
thumb-sized piece of ginger
1 tsp curry powder
1 tsp ground turmeric
1/2 tsp garam masala powder
15 oz crushed tomatoes
2 cups water
6.5 oz coconut milk
rice to serve
coriander to garnish

Wash the lentils under running water.

Chop the onion and grate the ginger.

Heat the olive oil in a big pot. Add the onion and ginger and saut√© for a
couple of minutes until the onions are softened. Add all the spices and cook
for another 1-2 minutes.

Add the tomatos, water and drained lentils into the pot and bring to a boil.
Cook over medium heat for about 20 minutes. Add the coconut milk and cook for
another 10 minutes.

Serve with cooked rice and garnish with fresh coriander.
